Amadou Diallo's tragic death led to the indictment of four officers who fired 41 shots, hitting him 19 times.
The officers believed Diallo was armed, but he was unarmed.
Diallo's family seeks justice, with his mother tearfully expressing the fight for accountability.
The defense argues the officers acted out of fear, not criminal intent.
The legal process involves reviewing grand jury proceedings and potential conflicts of interest among lawyers.
The community demands a fair trial, highlighting the ongoing struggle for police accountability in cases of excessive force.
The Diallo family's pursuit of justice remains a focal point amidst legal complexities.
